Precursor:
    ReactJS is a simple, feature-rich, component based JavaScript UI library. It can be used to develop small applications, as well as big complex applications.
        - It provides minimal and solid feature set to kick-start a web application.
        - Examples of websites that are powered by React includes Facebook, Instagram, Netflix, Code Academy, Reddit, etc.

(1) npx create-react-app .
        - With NodeJS/NPM installed on your machine, you can just run the following lines.
        - The project layout should include many files, such as "node_modules", ".gitignore", "package.json", and a "src file".

(2) npm start
    - This allows you to view your app as you are editing it; runs your app in development mode. The page will reload whenever it detecs any code change in the source files. Warnings and errors can be seen in the console. 

(3) npm i react-router-dom
    - Contains bindings for using React Router in web applications.

